explanation: The solution uses a depth-first search (DFS) approach to try to assign each number to a group. It first checks if the total sum of the array can be divided evenly by k and if the largest number is not greater than the target sum. The DFS function tries to assign each number to a group and backtracks if it cannot find a valid assignment. The use of sorting and pruning techniques improves the efficiency of the solution.

